Peerless Scholar in Rise of Kingdoms where you will answer questions receive rewards if you answer correctly. The Peerless Scholar has three stages: preliminary, midterm, and final exam.

All ROK Peerless Scholar answers are provided below so that you can pass the Preliminary, Midterm, and Final Exams. If you pass the Final Exam, you will receive a large number of gems.

Peerless Scholar Guide

Check all rise of kingdoms codes to get additional rewards.

Preliminary

  • Starts from Monday to Friday, 0:00 to 23:00 UTC.
  • Maintenance from 23:00 to 0:00
  • Your City Hall must be at least Level 10
  • One Preliminary try each day
  • Maximum of 3 Midterm Life Tokens may be earned each week.

Midterm

  • Starts Saturdays at 02:30 and 12:30.
  • Two Midterm sessions throughout the event.
  • Player may only attend one session at a time.
  • To qualify for the Midterm you must correctly answer 6 or more questions.
  • Governors may enter and wait at the answering panel for 5 minutes before the Midterm begins
  • Governors can no longer join the panel if responding has already started.

Final Exam

  • The Final Exam is made up of 15 multiple-choice questions with a time limit.
  • Governors must finish the response selection within the allotted time.
  • The erroneous response will be regarded as choosing an incorrect answer or failing to choose an answer on time.
  • The timing for questions 1–5 is 15 seconds, the timer for questions 6–10 is 12 seconds, and the timer for questions 11–15 is 10 seconds.
  • Governors will be disqualified if they respond wrong after they have used up all of their Life Tokens.
  • Governors who qualify for the Final Exam will get 3 Final Exam Life Tokens right away.
